      "description": "Second replicate in-vitro experiment at the nominal operating point (5 L/min, 3000 RPM). Predicted RH = 0.81; measured RH = 0.83; relative error 2.4%. Consistent agreement with experiment 1 supports model fidelity at this condition."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-nominal-exp3",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Nominal operating point experiment 3 — hemolysis index comparison",
      "description": "Third replicate in-vitro experiment at the nominal operating point (5 L/min, 3000 RPM). Predicted RH = 0.81; measured RH = 0.85; relative error 4.7%. Combined with experiments 1 and 2, all three experiments at the nominal operating point demonstrate that the CFD model reliably predicts hemolysis within the acceptance band. On the basis of these three experiments, the model is considered validated for the full operating range of five flow-speed combinations defined in the COU."
    }
